race.description: Bottle-O Swan Hill Xmas Races Sunday 23 Nov Hcp
race.comment: PRINCESS TORO (2) was well supported resuming over 1300m at Bendigo and proved too strong scoring by 1.3L. She jumped a short-priced favourite and spiked her figures. Gets in well with the 3kg claim and has the early speed to manage the awkward gate. Strips fitter and can win again. APPARATUS (3) rates well on his placed effort at Warrnambool first-up, where he settled well back from a wide barrier. He's placed 2/2 second-up and Coffey will give him every chance. BAVETTE (6) made up plenty of ground placing here first-up. Has been kept up to the mark with a winning jumpout and John Allen sticks from that. BAKERSBEND (8) deserved the comfortable Maiden win here heavily-backed and is sure to build on that. Has an outside barrier today but the promising galloper should be good enough to cope.
